<ul class="task-constraints">
<li><b>Time limit:</b> 1.00 s</li>
<li><b>Memory limit:</b> 512 MB</li>
</ul>
<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1676">
There are $n$ cities and initially no roads between them. However, every day a new road will be constructed, and there will be a total of $m$ roads.<br />
<br />
A component is a group of cities where there is a route between any two cities using the roads. After each day, your task is to find the number of components and the size of the largest component.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line has two integers $n$ and $m$: the number of cities and roads. The cities are numbered $1,2,\dots,n$.<br />
<br />
Then, there are $m$ lines describing the new roads. Each line has two integers $a$ and $b$: a new road is constructed between cities $a$ and $b$.<br />
<br />
You may assume that every road will be constructed between two different cities.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print $m$ lines: the required information after each day.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 10^5$<br />
<li>$1 \le m \le 2 \cdot 10^5$<br />
<li>$1 \le a,b \le n$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>5 3<br />
1 2<br />
1 3<br />
4 5</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>4 2<br />
3 3<br />
2 3</code>    </div>
